  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Drinfeld double <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="fraktur">D</mi></math> of the bosonization of a finite-dimensional Nichols algebra <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="fraktur">B</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>V</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> over a finite non-abelian group G is called a quantum group at a non-abelian group . We introduce Verma modules over such a quantum group <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="fraktur">D</mi></math> and prove that a Verma module has simple head and simple socle. This provides two bijective correspondences between the set of simple modules over <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="fraktur">D</mi></math> and the set of simple modules over the Drinfeld double <math altimg="si297.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="fraktur">D</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> . As an example, we describe the lattice of submodules of the Verma modules over the quantum group at the symmetric group <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> attached to the 12-dimensional Fomin–Kirillov algebra, computing all the simple modules and calculating their dimensions.</subfield>
